
Curl can be used to 'sign up' or authenticate, as such:

Create account through curl:
curl -v --header "Content-Type: application/json" --request POST --data '{"name":"xyz","password":"xyz","email":"a@foo.com"}' http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/signup


Login through curl:
curl -v --header "Content-Type: application/json" --request POST -u a@foo.com:xyz http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login

Returns JSON web token

